                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <origDate notBefore="1682" notAfter="1694">1682–1694</origDate>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            The manuscript originally belonged to <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14566ZawaldaMaryam">Zawalda Māryām</persName> 
                            (see, e.g., <locus target="#154ra #190v"/>).
                            It was acquired by an unknown missionary of
                            Evangeliska fosterlandsstiftelsen and brought to Sweden at some point between <date when="1866">1866</date>
                            (when the first missionaries connected to Evangeliska fosterlandsstiftelsen arrived in Ethiopia) and
                            <date when="1928">1928</date>, when it was catalogued in Sweden. During a period, 
                            the manuscript was kept at <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS1020EFSmissionsmuseum">Evangeliska Fosterlands-Stiftelsens etnografiska missionsmuseum</placeName> in 
                            Johannelund (Ulvsunda,  <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7456Stockholm">Stockholm</placeName>). 
                                After being catalogued by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6337Lofgren">Oscar Anders Valfrid Löfgren</persName> in <date when="1928">1928</date>,
                            apparently in Uppsala (<bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/W7HE9FNZ"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Loefgren1929Evangeliska"/><title level="a">Die abessinischen Handschriften der Evangeliska Fosterlands-Stiftelsen, Stockholm</title><title level="j">Le Monde Oriental</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Oscar</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Löfgren</t:surname></author><date>1929</date><biblScope unit="volume">23</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">1-22</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">1</citedRange></bibl>),
                            the manuscript was given by Evangeliska fosterlandsstiftelsen to <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14565ErlingEidem">
                                <title>Archbishop</title>
                                Erling Eidem</persName>.
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>In <date when="1964">1964</date>, 
                            <persName role="bequeather" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14565ErlingEidem">Erling Eidem</persName>
                            donated the manuscript to its current repository.</acquisition>
                    </history>
                    
